item.title: A Novel Visual Illusion Paradigm Provides Evidence for a General Factor of Illusion Sensitivity and Personality Correlates
The Structure of Chaos: An Empirical Comparison of Fractal Physiology Complexity Indices Using NeuroKit2
An-Shu Te
item.description: An Shu graduated from University of Singapore with a Bachelor of Arts (Honours) in Psychology with First Class Honours in 2019. Her research interests lie in Clinical Psychology, particularly with regards to dysfunctions in emotion regulatory and cognitive control processes in children. She also has a keen interest in studying specific disorders such as Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder, Eating Disorders and Personality Disorders.
